        <li><strong>Used Machinery Specialists:</strong> We value equipment based on its work capacity, not just its age.</li>
        <li><strong>Fast 48-Hour Approval:</strong> We know that "time is money." If you have a project starting next week, you can't wait a month for a bank.</li>
        <li><strong>Understanding Local Realities:</strong> We know how Malaysian businesses work—from festive season cash flow dips to supplier credit terms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common Questions About Machinery Purchase Loans</h2>

      <h3>"Can a new startup apply for a machinery loan?"</h3>
      <p>Yes, but it's harder. You'll likely need a director with strong personal income or some form of collateral. At Ing Heng, we often support startups if the directors have experience in the industry.</p>

      <h3>"What is the typical tenure for a machinery loan?"</h3>
      <p>Most industrial hire purchase agreements in Malaysia range from 3 to 5 years. For very high-value equipment, some terms can go up to 7 years.</p>

      <h3>"Is there a penalty for early settlement?"</h3>
      <p>Most agreements have a formula for interest rebates if you settle early. Always check your agreement for "Rule of 78" or other settlement terms.</p>

